author: Russell Brand
description:
The heroic war narrative collapses when money, power, and history are traced instead of slogans repeated. As corruption scandals circle Zelensky’s inner circle, the same patterns seen in Vietnam, Iraq, and Iran-Contra re-emerge: oversight dismantled, aid siphoned, and legacy media pivoting only once denial becomes impossible. This isn’t about Ukraine alone, but about how democracy is marketed while corruption is tolerated whenever geopolitical leverage is at stake.
